-- Regulators Loosen IPO Rules for Commercial Banks, Securities Journal Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-31T23:20:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-31/regulators-loosen-ipo-rules-for-commercial-banks-securities-journal-says.html
China’s banking and securities
regulators have relaxed rules on initial public offerings by the
nation’s city commercial banks, the China Securities Journal
reported today, citing an unidentified person.  City banks which had more than 200 shareholders prior to
2006 will now be allowed to apply to list shares, the report
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  